txt.en: Honey jars can be found in Limlók.\n\nYou should fill up the empty honey jars.
Trygvar, son of Runerik and Yrsa, has not eaten honey in over a day.
Honey can be found at the forest's edge in the eastern reaches of the Floodfells.\n\nYou should gather honey for Limlók.
'It has been well over a whole day since I last ate some honey!'

'It has been a whole day! It has been well over a whole day since I last ate some honey! It is my favourite food, after all. I am not sure I can go much longer without that sweet nectar. I am not allowed to venture too far from Limlók right now or I'd head to the forest's edge to retrieve some. Perhaps you would be kind enough to gather some honey for me? Some extra for the village would certainly raise spirits in Limlók! I would watch out for the bees though. The Taurogrim have angered most every creature living at the forest's edge.'
Place the honey in jars at Limlók ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
